          "body": "The chapter is architecturally a diptych. Days 1-3 are days of *separation and forming*: light from darkness (day 1), waters above from waters below (day 2), seas from dry land with vegetation (day 3). Days 4-6 are days of *populating and filling*: sun, moon, stars to inhabit the light-domain (day 4); fish and birds to inhabit the sea-and-sky-domain (day 5); land animals and humans to inhabit the land-and-vegetation-domain (day 6). The pairing is exact — day 1 ↔ day 4, day 2 ↔ day 5, day 3 ↔ day 6. The structure resolves v. 2's twin problem: the earth was *tohu* (formless, no shape) — fixed by days 1-3; and *bohu* (void, no inhabitants) — fixed by days 4-6. This is not modern science slipped into ancient prose; it is theological architecture: God's character is order, and His creative act moves from chaos toward kingdom."
